After spending two years in retirement, Nigeria’s former Commonwealth and Olympics boxer, Nestor Bolum is making a comeback to the ring, with his eyes set on the World Boxing Federation (WBF) title in a showdown against Tyson Lantry on November 16 in Sydney, Australia. The post Ex-Nigerian Olympian Nestor Bolum set for WBF title fight in Sydney appeared first on The Guardian Nigeria News – Nigeria and World News. Source: Guardian